        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8347",
        "content": "Where is the young man, the son of yonder magnanimous King?\" And quoth the Wazir, \"O mighty King, thou didst command him be put to death.\" When the King heard this, he was clean distraught and cried out from his heart's core and in most of head, saying, \"Woe to you!",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-low_s-slow_e-low",
        "gender": "M",
