        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8347",
        "content": "She had Nature kohl'd eyes, heavy hips and thighs and waist of slenderest guise, her sight healed all maladies and quenched the fire of sighs, for she was even as the poet cries,",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-low_s-slow_e-low",
        "gender": "M",
